{"to":["mark@helpinghandscharity.org"],"subject":"Exploring Partnership Opportunities between SecureNow Insurance & Helping Hands","body":"Hi Mark,

I hope you’re doing well. I wanted to reach out and follow up on our earlier conversations about ways SecureNow Insurance and Helping Hands Charity might collaborate.

Our team has been developing an initiative that would combine SecureNow’s insurance expertise with Helping Hands’ on-the-ground community support to assist families impacted by natural disasters. The idea is to create a clear framework for:
• Rapid needs assessment and emergency relief
• Short-term financial assistance for affected households
• Longer-term recovery resources, such as rebuilding guidance and risk-mitigation education

We believe a joint program could amplify the impact of both organizations, provide demonstrable community benefit, and serve as a model for future business-nonprofit partnerships.

Would you be available for a brief call next week to discuss the concept and outline next steps? I’m currently free on Tuesday (10–11 a.m. or 3–4 p.m.) and Thursday (1–3 p.m.) but can be flexible if another time works better for you.

Looking forward to hearing your thoughts.

Best regards,
Jane Smith
Senior Insurance Agent
SecureNow Insurance
